# SearchBard Python Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your credentials

# =============================================================================
# Firebase Configuration
# =============================================================================
# Get these values from Firebase Console > Project Settings > Service Accounts
# Download the service account JSON file and reference its path here
FIREBASE_CREDENTIALS_PATH=path/to/your/firebase-service-account.json

# Or provide individual Firebase configuration values:
FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
FIREBASE_DATABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.firebaseio.com
FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project-id.appspot.com

# =============================================================================
# Web Scraping Configuration (Optional)
# =============================================================================
# API endpoints or additional service credentials can be added here
# Example: SCRAPING_API_KEY=your_scraping_api_key_here

# =============================================================================
# Notes
# =============================================================================
# 
# Firebase Setup Instructions:
# 1. Go to Firebase Console: https://console.firebase.google.com/
# 2. Create a new project or select existing project
# 3. Go to Project Settings > Service Accounts
# 4. Click "Generate New Private Key" to download JSON file
# 5. Save the JSON file securely (DO NOT commit to version control)
# 6. Set FIREBASE_CREDENTIALS_PATH to the absolute path of this file
# 7. Or copy individual values to the variables above
#
# Free Tier Limits:
# - Firebase Realtime Database: 1GB storage, 10GB/month transfer
# - Firebase Firestore: 1GB storage, 50K reads/day, 20K writes/day
# - Firebase Storage: 5GB storage, 1GB/day transfer
#
# Security Notes:
# - Never commit .env or service account JSON files to version control
# - .env and *.json should be in .gitignore
# - Rotate credentials regularly
# - Use Firebase Security Rules to protect your data
